  <question type="stack">
    <name>
      <text>Factorising a monic quadratic expression</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>Factorise the following quadratic expression:
\[
{@expr@}
\]
</p>

<p>[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
We want to factorise:
</p>

<p>
\[
{@expr@}
\]
</p>

<p>
Step 1: Identify the coefficient of \(x\) and the constant term.
</p>

<p>
The coefficient of \(x\) is \({@a + b@}\) and the constant term is \({@a*b@}\).
</p>

<p>
Step 2: Find two numbers that:
</p>

<ul>
<li>multiply to give \({@a*b@}\)</li>
<li>add to give \({@a + b@}\)</li>
</ul>

<p>
The numbers are \({@a@}\) and \({@b@}\) because:
</p>

<p>
\[
{@a@} \times {@b@} = {@a*b@}
\]
</p>

<p>
\[
{@a@} + {@b@} = {@a + b@}
\]
</p>

<p>
Step 3: Write the factorised form:
</p>

<p>
\[
(x + {@a@})(x + {@b@})
\]
</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
